        "renderShape": {
          "kind": "markdown"
        },
        "markdown": "# Declaration Primitive\n\nThe declaration is the graph handshake. It names the graph, states what it is, and exposes the surfaces that other nodes can consume.",
        "_placement": {
          "version": 1,
          "state": "manually-shaped",
          "source": "manual",
          "updatedAt": 1780528341211,
          "reason": "node-drag"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "declaration-primitive-note",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "What Declaration Owns",
      "root": true,
      "position": {
        "x": 180,
        "y": -220
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-basic-primitives-declaration"
        },
        "markdown": "## What declaration does\n\nUse `declaration` when a graph needs an identity and an addressable surface contract.\n\nIt owns:\n- `identity`\n- `intent`\n- `declaration`\n\nThose fields tell Twilite and every consuming portal what this graph is and which surfaces it exposes."
      }
    },
